headline: This 4.7%-Yielding Dividend Stock Has High-Octane Growth Coming Down the Pipeline Through 2028
summary: Oneok has grown briskly over the past decade.  Oneok (NYSE: OKE) is a bit of an outlier.  The energy infrastructure company has a high-yielding dividend (recently around 4.7%) and a high earnings growth rate (more than 10% annually).
